wow! 👽 Minute colloidal particles of Glacial Marine Mud act as an emulsifying agent by forming a barrier around oily particles, thus allowing them to be removed. This skin renewing estuary treasure helps exfoliate dead skin cells, remove skin contaminants, and rejuvenate damaged or troubled skin. Softens and purifies the skin. By attracting water, the mud helps to hydrate the skin. 💦 It nurtures your skin with more than 50 beneficial minerals and trace elements, including zinc and sea botanicals. Helps draw out impurities and toxins. The basic molecular structure of Glacial Marine Mud is negatively charged. 🔋 Positive ions including cations that naturally occur in the mud and positively charged impurities bind to the mud’s negative charge and can then be rinsed away leaving skin cleansed and detoxified. Micro fat grafting or fat transfer can be used to augment the shape, size and suppleness of breasts and can be performed as a standalone procedure, or in combination with breast augmentation and Mastopexy surgery. If you are looking for a more natural alternative to breast implants surgery, or if you desire a more voluptuous and soft breast contour, then micro fat grafting may be an option for you. During your consultation, Dr. Adibfar can discuss this option and work with you to ensure a treatment plan that is uniquely suited to meet your cosmetic goals.
